Dating: 22ND DYNASTY (not before); 25TH DYNASTY AND CONTEMPORARIES (not after)
Name: Canopic jar with no lid
Description: The body of the vessel has curved walls, which taper towards a broad base. The wide rim is bevelled slightly on the inside. The bottom is only roughly smoothened; inside, only the upper third is hollowed out in a cylindrical shape. On the front is an inscription in black ink.
